Ask Question¶

  • Can we predict the survival time base on clinical and demogaphic data ?

  • Can we predict death cause base on clinical and demogaphic data ?

The data we have available are the clinical and demogaphic datas. These datas were collected from 1935 to 2018 (83 years) at the Centre for Addiction and Mental Health Toronto (http://www.camh.ca/)

def plot_feature_importances(df, threshold = 0.95):
    """
    Plots 15 most frequent variable and the cumulative sum of frequency
    Prints the number of variable needed to reach threshold cumulative frequency.
    
    Parameters
    --------
    df : dataframe
        Dataframe of variable frequency. Columns must be variable frequency
    threshold : float, default = 0.9
        Threshold for prining information about cumulative frequency
        
    Return
    --------
    df : dataframe
        Dataframe ordered by feature frequency with a normalized column (sums to 1)
        and a cumulative frequency column
    
    """
    
    plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 18
    
    
    f,ax=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(30,12))
    #plt.figure(figsize = (10, 6))
    #ax = plt.subplot()
    
    # Need to reverse the index to plot most important on top
    ax[0].barh(list(reversed(list(df.index[:20]))), 
            df['freq_normalized'].head(20), 
            align = 'center', edgecolor = 'k')
    
    # Set the yticks and labels
    ax[0].set_yticks(list(reversed(list(df.index[:20]))))
    ax[0].set_yticklabels(df['cause_death_list'].head(20))
    
    

    # Plot labeling
    ax[0].set_title('Death cause frequency  normalized')
    ax[0].set_ylabel('Normalized Frequency')

    #plt.xlabel('Normalized Importance'); plt.title('Feature Importances')
    #plt.show()
   
    importance_index = np.min(np.where(df['cumsum'] > threshold))
    # Cumulative importance plot
    #plt.figure(figsize = (8, 10))
    plt.plot(list(range(len(df))), df['cumsum'], 'r-')
    #plt.xlabel('Number of Features'); plt.ylabel('Cumulative Importance'); 
    ax[1].set_title('Cumulative Death cause frequency ')
    ax[1].set_ylabel('Cumulative Frequency')
    ax[1].set_xlabel('Number of death causes')
    #plt.title('Cumulative Feature Importance');
    #plt.axhline(y=threshold, color='b', linestyle='-', label= )
    draw() # necessary to render figure before saving
    #plt.show();
    f.savefig(imagedir+'death_cause.svg',bbox_inches='tight')
    
    print('%d variables required for %0.2f of cumulative frequency' % (importance_index + 1, threshold))
    
    return 0
